f=Brand Studio/tempo/agent.md · p=Tempo fourth definer, sound: per-brand sonic guide (music mood ranges, tone derived atlas's kit, lena's register, weave's arc sound never contradicts brand) usage-licensing discipline verifies track's license against actual use, registers append-only, sweeps expiries lapsed subscription can't quietly strand live videos. Rights gate fit: nothing selectable until it's cleared. businesses doing audio content, tempo explicit, documented no-op. · po=Eleventh final Brand Studio agent. Pixel pulse invoke whenever produced content carries audio (selection license ref travel manifest); license spend routes operator board's gate thresholds; audio coherence joins spark's gate references once brand's guide exists (dormant line until then); jurisdiction counsel questions operator's, always. · sr=\| Skill \| Location \| One-line purpose \| · sr=\|---\|---\|---\| · sr=\| sound-identity \| `custom/` (+ sonic-guide template) \| The sonic guide per brand: testable mood/VO statements derived from the other definers, registry-only selection, drift flagged, operator-owned amendments. \| · sr=\| usage-licensing \| `custom/` (+ license-registry template) \| Rights discipline: verify the quoted license text against the actual use (paid ads and monetized platforms are the classic exclusions), register append-only, sweep expiries, route ambiguity up with the clause. **Catalog's marketplace slot converted to custom** — the search found only musician-side skills; flagged in frontmatter. \| · sr=Full routing: `operational/skill/tempo-skill-routing.md`. · h2:Skill Chain (summary)=`audio need (pixel/pulse) → usage-licensing (may we? — cleared + registered) \· → sound-identity (should we? — guide fit) → selection + license ref in the manifest \· → expiry sweeps on cadence \· lapses flag live uses → operator` · id=None spark Brand Studio's leader. empty `identity/` folder intentional. · ol=\| Subfolder \| File \| Summary \| · ol=\|---\|---\|---\| · ol=\| skill \| `